                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Indenture (Marriage settlement).</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_111286">Clewer (Berkshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1347">21 Ed. III. August 4, 1347</origDate>. Indenture between Sir John de Brocas on one part, and Walter Whithors and
                        Isabella Barry on the other part, reciting grant by the former of £20 rent
                        in Clewer, and conditioning it on the marriage of these persons; but that it
                        is only to come into effect after marriage if they lose the several
                        properties in Nottinghamshire which he had given them (deed not found), and
                        if they have made every effort at law to defend themselves against any claim
                        of the brothers of Isabella.</p>
                  </msItem>
